<br>
Wondering whether an upgrade to Wavecrasher would be worthwhile?<br>
<br>
What is Wavecrasher taunt like and if I do upgrade, which weapon should I keep to go with it?<br>
<br>
All advice greatfully rec'd.<br>
<br>
Rathsar Ironforge<br>
54 Champion, Lanys. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaellewyndemere>Gaelle Wyndemere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 5:54:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4941.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon advice</span><hr size=1> I think the upgrade to a Wavecrasher is a great idea. Procs a slow, which tends to upset mobs quite a bit. A Wavecrasher will serve as a great aggro weapon into your 60's until you can upgrade to a Willsapper or better.<br>
<br>
I would also suggest dropping the mallet and keeping the Frosty. The damage/dly is better suited for an offhand wep and the cold/cold debuff proc would add a bit more aggro to your side.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rathsar>rathsar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 6:00:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4941.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon advice</span><hr size=1> Thanks Gaelle, much appreciated.<br>
<br>
Now my next query - the only way I can upgrade is to downgrade my haste.<br>
<br>
Currently have Spiked Seahorse Belt and I was thinking of downgrading to RBG and using the extra cash to get Wavecraher and upgrade my shoulder slot and back slot (currently using Enchanted Dwarven Pauldrons and Dire Wolf Cloak) - upgrade would be to Cloak of Maelstrom and Barbed Dragon Pauldrons.<br>
<br>
What do you reckon pls?<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
<br>
Rath. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jonnaspovar>Jonnas Povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 6:11:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4941.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon advice</span><hr size=1> If you're on CoV, get draconic pauldrons for free. If not, I'd suggest a higher-end dragonwing mantle, if you have the cash (peerless is very nice) my 2cp. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69159"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/jonnaspovar/jonsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rathsar>rathsar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 6:35:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4941.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon advice</span><hr size=1> Sadly my downgrade on haste with probably generate around 25 to 30K and I will only have 5K or so for the shoulder slot.<br>
<br>
On Lanys, I will be lucky to get the Barbed Dragon ones for that money.<br>
<br>
Believe it or not I have almost exclusively hunted in Luclin and PoP at higher levels, so my factions will be whatever Dwarven, Brell Serrilis starts at.<br>
<br>
Cheers.<br>
<br>
Rath. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaellewyndemere>Gaelle Wyndemere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 11:44:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4941.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon advice</span><hr size=1> Jonnas has the right idea, dont spend money on shoulders, go blow a some hours in Kael and get warmly (i finished the quest at warmly anyway) to CoV and get the Draconic Pauldrons. No sense in blowing cash on a slot you can fill for free with a nice item if ya just spend some time factioning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rathsar>rathsar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/03 4:11:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4941.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon advice</span><hr size=1> Okey Dokey, I hate giants so that suits me fine.<br>
